    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-06-04T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-06-04T13:00:00-05:00" n="724"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d724">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">501.BB Palestine/5–2849: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Legation in Switzerland</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d724fn1">This telegram was repeated to London and
                        Cairo.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-06-04T14:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 4, 1949—2 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Unpal1">Unpal</gloss> 133. For <gloss target="#t_USDel1"
                        >USDel</gloss>, Lausanne. For your info only, since <gloss target="#t_USG1"
                        >USG</gloss> regards refugee problem as overriding factor in determining
                    eventual disposition Gaza strip (<gloss target="#t_Palun1">Palun</gloss> 174 May
                    28), <gloss target="#t_USG1">USG</gloss> would approve incorporation area in
                    Israel as part final territorial settlement provided this cld be achieved by
                    negot with and full consent Egyptian Govt and provided territorial compensation
                    made to Egypt according Pres’ formula if Egypt desires such compensation. Event
                    transfer to Israel, <gloss target="#t_USG1">USG</gloss> considers fol provisions
                    wld be essential to safeguard refugees and residents Gaza strip: (1) clear and
                    unequivocal assurances by Israeli Govt concerning acceptance refugees and
                    resident population Gaza strip as legitimate cits Israel with same rights and
                    same protection accorded Jewish cits, and Israeli Govt undertaking that its
                    civil and military authorities will respect spirit and letter of such
                    assurances; (2) provision for UN supervision of transfer of area and of
                    subsequent status and treatment of population for appropriate period of
                    time.</p>
                <p>In opinion Emb Cairo (<gloss target="#t_Palun1">Palun</gloss> 181 June 2) without
                    consulting Egyptian auths, Egypt might well be willing cede Gaza strip to <pb
                        facs="1107" n="1091" xml:id="pg_1091"/> Israel provided latter assumes
                    refugee burden, since area wld ultimately become administrative and financial
                    liability to Egypt. Azzam Pasha<note n="2" xml:id="d724fn2">Secretary-General of
                        the Arab League.</note> (Cairo <gloss target="#t_A1">A–</gloss>565 May
                        16<note n="3" xml:id="d724fn3">Not printed.</note> rptd you) expressed
                    similar views. Emb considers it probable Egyptian Govt wld reserve final
                    decision until formal peace negots and wld use as bargaining point.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Webb</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
